Here's a Java solution:
```java
public boolean isPowerOfTwo(int n) {
    int low = 0, high = 31;
    while (low <= high) {
        int mid = (low + high) / 2;
        if (2^mid == n) {
            return true;
        } else if (2^mid < n) {
            low = mid + 1;
        } else {
            high = mid - 1;
        }
    }
    return false;
}
```
This solution uses the same approach as the previous one, but with the modification that it uses 2^x instead of 3^x.

